    "content": "The Late Shaykh Kafami, in his book, Baladul Ameen has narrated a dua from Ameerul Momineen (a.s.). Whenever a person in difficult circumstances will recite this Dua, the Almighty shall solve his problems. The Dua is as follows:\r\n\r\n--بِسْمِ اللهِ الرَّحْمٰنِ الرَّحِیْمِ یَا عِمَادَ مَنْ لَا عِمَادَ لَہٗ، وَ یَا ذُخْرَ مَنْ لَا ذُخْرَ لَہٗ، وَ یَا سَنَدَ مَنْ لَا سَنَدَ لَہٗ، وَ یَا حِرْزَ مَنْ لَا حِرْزَ لَہٗ، وَ یَا غِیَاثَ مَنْ لَا غِیَاثَ لَہٗ، وَ یَا كَنْزَ مَنْ لَا كَنْزَ لَہٗ، وَ یَا عِزَّ مَنْ لَا عِزَّ لَہٗ، یَا كَرِیْمَ الْعَفْوِ، یَا حَسَنَ التَّجَاوُزِ، یَا عَوْنَ الضُّعَفَاۤءِ، یَا كَنْزَ الْفُقَرَاۤءِ، یَا عَظِیْمَ الرَّجَاۤءِ، یَا مُنْقِذَ الْغَرْقیٰ، یَا مُنْجِیَ الْھَلْكیٰ، یَا مُحْسِنُ یَا مُجْمِلُ یَا مُنْعِمُ یَا مُفْضِلُ، اَنْتَ الَّذِیْ سَجَدَ لَكَ سَوَادُ اللَّیْلِ وَ نُوْرُ النَّھَارِ وَ ضَوْءِ الْقَمَرِ وَ شُعَاعُ الشَّمْسِ وَ خَفِیْفُ الشَّجَرِ وَ دَوِیُّ الْمَاۤءِ، یَاۤ اَﷲُ یَاۤ اَﷲُ یَاۤ اَﷲُ، لَاۤ اِلٰہَ اِلَّاۤ اَنْتَ، وَحْدَكَ لَا شَرِیْكَ لَكَ، یَا رَبَّاہُ یَاۤ اَﷲُ، صَلِّ عَلیٰ مُحَمَّدٍ وَ اٰلِ مُحَمَّدٍ، وَ افْعَلْ بِنَا مَاۤ اَنْتَ اَھْلُہٗ۔--After this ask for your legitimate desires.", 
    "audio": "", 
    "transliteration": "The Late Shaykh Kafami, in his book, Baladul Ameen has narrated a dua from Ameerul Momineen (a.s.). Whenever a person in difficult circumstances will recite this Dua, the Almighty shall solve his problems. The Dua is as follows:\r\n\r\nBISMILLAAHIR RAHMAANIR RAHEEM YAA E'MAADA MAN LAA E'MAADA LAHU, WA YAA ZUKHRA MAN LAA ZUKHRA LAHU, WA YAA SANADA MAN LAA SANADA LAHU, WA YAA HIRZA MAN LAA HIRZA LAHU, WA YAA GHEYAASA MAN LAA GHEYAASA LAHU, WA YAA KANZA MAN LAA KANZA LAHU, WA YAA I'ZZA MAN LAA I'ZZA LAHU, YAA KAREEMAL A'FWE, YAA HASANAT TAJAA-WOZE, YAA A'WNAZ ZO-A'FAA-E, YAA KANZAL FOQARAA-E, YAA A'ZEEMAR RAJAA-E, YAA MUNQEZAL GHARQAA, YAA MUNJEYAL HALKAA, YAA MOHSENO YAA MUJMELO YAA MUN-E'MO YAA MUFZELO, ANTAL LAZEE SAJADA LAKA SAWAADUL LAYLE WA NOORUN NAHAARE WA ZAW-UL QAMARE WA SHO-A'A-O'SH SHAMSE WA KHAFEEFUSH SHAJARE WA DAWIYYUL MAA-E, YAA ALLAAHO, YAA ALLAAHO, YAA ALLAAHO, LAA ELAAHA ILLAA ANTA, WAHDAKA LAA SHAREEKA LAKA, YAA RABBAAHO YAA ALLAAHO, SALLE A'LAA MOHAMMADIN WA AALE MOHAMMADIN, WAF-A'L BENAA MAA ANTA AHLOHU.\r\n\r\nAfter this ask for your legitimate desires.", 
    "english": "The Late Shaykh Kafami, in his book, Baladul Ameen has narrated a dua from Ameerul Momineen (a.s.). Whenever a person in difficult circumstances will recite this Dua, the Almighty shall solve his problems. The Dua is as follows:\r\n\r\nO Support of him who lacks support! O Hoard of him who lacks hoard! O Prop of him who lacks prop! O Shelter of him who lacks shelter! O Aid of him who is aidless! O Treasure of him who has no treasure! O Might of him who wants might! O He Who pardons generously! O He Who overlooks excellently! O Helper of the weak! O Treasure of the poor! O He Who is greatly hoped! O Savior of the drowned! O Rescuer of the perishing! O All-munificent! O All- benign! O All-gracious! O All-benevolent! It is You alone before Whom the darkness of night has prostrated. So have the light of day, the brightness of the moon, the radiance of the sun, the rustle of trees, and the murmur of water. O Allah! O Allah! O Allah! There is no god save You; You are the One and Only without having any partner. O my Lord! O Allah! (Please do) bless Muhammad and the Household of Muhammad and do to us all that which suits You.</b></i></font>\r\n\r\nAfter this ask for your legitimate desires."
}